Text: Whoaaa...!
Delta!
I-I'm fine! I won't get blown away so easily!
I'll show it...that I'm the stronger one!
Hahh?!
Tch... I can't get close enough!
Ack...!

Looks like its strategy is to use the force of the
wind to prevent its opponents from getting near.

Then it lets countless feathers fly like arrows,
weakening its opponent to the point of
exhaustion before crushing them.
Delta! Observe your opponent closely!
Observe...closely...!
...It's a big bird!
Not quite what I was getting at...
And...it's got skinny legs!

Indeed. It might be a good strategy to aim for its
limbs.

But that only goes for when it's on the ground. 
You'll need to finish it before it flies off.
It can't hit me anymore!
You've actually got a pretty sharp eye, Delta!

Observing prey is a fundamental part of hunting. My
guess is she knows what to do out of pure instinct.

It doesn't want me to get close...so that's
exactly...what I'm gonna do!
Hyaaaah!
Bwaaahh! *cough* Ngh... You stupid bird!

She thrust her claws into the ground and is closing
the distance to avoid getting blown back. It's a
primitive tactic, but it could work—
Hrrrrahh... You can't...blow me...away!

But keeping one hand stuck to the ground makes her
an easy target. What're you going to do, Delta—?
...Grarrrrr!

Well played. She's thought this one out, or perhaps
she's relying on her hunter's instincts.

She's amongst the best in the Seven Shadows when it
comes to her split-second fighting instincts and her
firepower when delivering a decisive blow.
Shadow once described Delta as...
...a "suicide weapon"!
Eat...thiiiis...!

It can't fly properly now that you've taken out its
legs—you've beat it.
Grrraaaaarrr!!!
Wow...looks like you really went all out.

Hey, you're late, kitty cat! I already hunted down
all the prey!
I see... Good job.

You too, Zeta. I'm guessing you made your way through
the cave. What was it like inside?

Looks like that dead bird ravaged the place—it's a
wreck. Well, we may still find something if we spend
enough time looking.
Ahahah! You were useless for this mission, kitty cat!

Look...I was responsible for blocking the enemy's
escape route.

Still, you didn't hunt down a single prey! Which
means I'm stronger than you!

Yup, sure, let's go with that—although the same
definitely can't be said about your mental capacity.
Hey! You're making fun of me again!

This is why I don't bother with you, doggie. Alpha,
I'll leave it to the Garden members to investigate
the hideout. See you around.
Hold on, Zeta!
Hey! You get back here, kitty cat!

...Make sure you're both back by dinner the day after
tomorrow!

Yeah, they definitely didn't hear that... I've still
got a long way to go as a leader.

Anyway, that damn kitty cat ended up getting away...
But I hunted down all the prey all by myself! I'm the
best, right?!
Heh... So you bared your fangs against the darkness.

Yup! Not sure what that means, but that's exactly
what I did!

(Delta doesn't really understand how to play the
whole shadowbroker scenario.)

(She seems to enjoy herself, even if she doesn't get
what's happening, but honestly, it can get a little
awkward on my part.)
Reward time, Boss man!
Hmm, let's see...

Let's try deep frying tempura with this magic fryer
Eta gave me.

This should turn out even better than last time.
You want to be the taste tester again, Delta?
Yeah, I wanna be the tempura taster!

(That said, Alpha and the others are really getting
into their pretend Shadow Garden roles these days.)
Alright, it's almost done frying.
Sooo excited...

This fryer is incredible—it hardly produces any
smoke.

(In that sense, it's a nice breather having Delta
here who doesn't seem to think much about
anything.)
Time to eeeat!
Hold on, Delta!
*munch*
It's so crispy and delicious!

(I just took it out of the boiling hot oil. How the
hell is she able to pick it up and eat it so
casually?)
Geez, you therianthropes are on another level.

Yup! We're super strong! Especially me—I've got
boundless energy!
...Here, open wide.
*munch*

C'mon, don't eat the chopsticks! And quit chewing on
my wrist!
Heheh... I'll be careful not to eat you, Boss man!

(...Delta reminds me of the dog I had in my previous
life.)
...Good puppy.
Boss man?
Want some more tempura, Delta?

Sure, Boss man! Let's eat until our bellies are
stuffed!
